
factoids about Markov numbers

From Zagier asymptotic limit is
m(n) = 1/3 exp C sqrt(n) for C=2.35234...

C = 2.3523414972
C^2 = 5.533510519449137
log C = 0.8554112138844506

log m = -log3 + C sqrt(n)
      = -log3 + C exp (0.5 log n)

So in the kth row of the tree, there are 2^k numbers
with 2^(k-1) < n < 2^k
so the k't row is

log m = -log3 + C exp (0.5 log 2^k)
      = -log3 + C exp (0.5 k log2)
      = -log3 + C 2^(k/2)
      = -log3 + C sqrt(2^k)

so this provides a natural normalization


